# The submit-news intake page ships TWO language variants (NL + EN)
# selected at first paint by ?lang=. To prevent stale CDN/browser
# copies from masking content fixes (e.g. the 2026-04-27 EN-form
# `hidden` regression), force revalidation on every load. Both URL
# forms map to the same asset on Cloudflare Pages — list both so
# the rule applies whether visitors hit the canonical .html path or
# the extensionless variant Wouter shares in outreach.
/submit-news.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
/submit-news
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

# Public HTML pages embed the header CTA markup directly (no shared
# include). After 2026-04-27 we shipped Variant A (command-card) and
# bumped the style.css/app.js cache-bust query so the new CSS rules
# can't be masked by a stale stylesheet. To make sure visitors who
# already have a cached HTML page from the legacy-pill era pick up
# the new HTML — and therefore the new ?v= asset URLs — force
# revalidation on every public HTML page that carries the masthead.
# This costs a 304 round-trip; it does not re-download the body.
/
